{"word":"προσυναπάντησις","slug":"προσυναπάντησις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n90243\" key=\"prosunapa/nthsis\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">προσυν-απάντησις</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">εως</itype>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen>, a rhet. figure, in which when two nouns are placed first the words belonging to the second precede those belonging to the first (as in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:4:450\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.450</biblScope> </bibl>), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0594.tlg002:2:27\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Alex.\">Alex.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Fig.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2.27</biblScope></bibl>.</entryFree>"}]}